Name: spondylocostal dysostosis
Definition: A dysostosis that results_in abnormal development located_in vertebrae or located_in ribs. The bones of the spine do not develop properly

Name: brachydactyly
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by short fingers and toes.

Name: obsolete Chlamydophila pneumoniae infectious disease
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by short fingers and toes.

Name: multiple synostoses syndrome
Definition: A dysostosis that is characterized by premature joint ankylosis and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inhertitance.

Name: acrofrontofacionasal dysostosis
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by intellectual disability

Name: acromelic frontonasal dysostosis
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by cranium bifidum

Name: acrofacial dysostosis
Definition: A hetergeneous dysostosis that is characterized by digital dysplasia

Name: Laurin-Sandrow syndrome
Definition: A dysostosis characterized by polysyndactyly of hands and/or feet

Name: synostosis
Definition: A dysostosis that results_in abnormal fusing of adjacent bones.

Name: acrodysostosis
Definition: A dysostosis that results_in shortening of interphalangeal joints located_in hand or located_in foot along with mental deficiency.
